For each 2 cups raw rice:

Steam the rice as normal but slightly tough.

3tsp salt
3tbsp sugar
3tbsp rice vinegar
2tbsp mirin
2tbsp sake

Heat and dissolve the salt and sugar.

Drizzle it into the rice in parts, folding the rice to coat each grain.

Continue folding the rice until steam no longer rises.

You can swap between sake and vinegar to adjust acidity.
